12:15.273 --> 12:17.107
- Hello.
- Oh, hey, Charlotte.

12:17.109 --> 12:19.075
- There she is!
- Hey.

12:19.077 --> 12:21.478
I just heard the score
of the Devils-Flyers game.

12:21.480 --> 12:24.414
Sorry, you lose. Peng-win!

12:24.416 --> 12:27.017
(laughter)

12:27.019 --> 12:29.219
I don't understand how this
bird is winning so much.

12:29.221 --> 12:30.420
Unless someone's helping him.

12:30.422 --> 12:31.588
Someone from the inside.

12:31.590 --> 12:33.456
If you weren't my boss,
I'd call you crazy.

12:33.458 --> 12:34.958
Charlotte, call him crazy.

12:36.527 --> 12:39.095
No, actually, I think
maybe Oscar's right.

12:39.097 --> 12:42.666
Maybe the penguin's got
a mole on the inside.

12:42.668 --> 12:44.935
An actual mole!

12:44.937 --> 12:46.169
(laughter)

12:46.171 --> 12:48.471
Damn, Char, you are bringing it!

12:48.473 --> 12:51.141
Ah-ah!

12:51.143 --> 12:53.443
Oscar, the show starts in a minute.

12:53.445 --> 12:55.645
Yeah, I'll be right back there.

12:55.647 --> 12:58.315
Did you see that?
I'm finally fitting in.

12:58.317 --> 12:59.397
They even called me "Char."

12:59.421 --> 13:01.585
That's, like, halfway to a nickname.

13:01.587 --> 13:03.787
Yeah, and all you had to do was

13:03.789 --> 13:06.756
- throw me under the bus.
- What?

13:06.758 --> 13:08.191
Just because they're being jerks

13:08.193 --> 13:10.694
doesn't mean you have to
go all Don Rickles on me.

13:10.696 --> 13:12.963
I wish somebody had my back.
I wish you had my back.

13:12.965 --> 13:15.298
Are you serious right now?

13:15.300 --> 13:17.867
Is all the yelling and
arm waving not clear?

13:19.103 --> 13:22.072
I'm sorry, I'm just in a bad place.

13:22.074 --> 13:24.274
Because of the penguin thing?

13:24.276 --> 13:26.710
I know it's silly, but
knowing sports is my job,

13:26.712 --> 13:28.411
and now I'm turning
into a laughing stock

13:28.413 --> 13:30.780
at the one thing I'm
supposed to be good at.

13:30.782 --> 13:32.916
If I lose that, what do I have?

13:32.918 --> 13:35.518
Oscar, I'm sorry.

13:35.520 --> 13:37.420
I didn't know it was
bothering you so much.

13:37.422 --> 13:39.322
That's because I'm good at hiding it.

13:39.324 --> 13:42.325
I've got many levels.

13:42.327 --> 13:43.827
Well, two.

13:45.796 --> 13:47.899
Oscar, the show starts in 30 seconds.

13:47.900 --> 13:49.318
Oh, and there's a zoo in Florida

13:49.401 --> 13:51.101
that wants to see if you
can outwit a manatee.

13:51.103 --> 13:52.583
But don't worry, I did some research,

13:52.607 --> 13:53.510
and they're real dumb.

13:53.512 --> 13:54.671
You probably can do it.

14:00.845 --> 14:02.912
(man clucking)

14:04.682 --> 14:07.617
Well, that doesn't sound
like a penguin at all.

14:07.619 --> 14:09.185
That sounds like a chicken,

14:09.187 --> 14:11.421
so the joke's on you.

14:11.423 --> 14:14.024
My point was you're
scared of the penguin,

14:14.026 --> 14:15.258
so you're a chicken.

14:16.694 --> 14:18.728
Oh, well, that's pretty good.

14:19.830 --> 14:22.332
Please tell me that's our last caller.

14:22.334 --> 14:24.901
Nope. Up next is Charlotte,
from Manhattan.

14:27.304 --> 14:29.739
Hello, Charlotte, you're on the air.

14:29.741 --> 14:31.474
Hi, Oscar.

14:31.476 --> 14:34.244
Everybody thinks
that penguin is so classy

14:34.246 --> 14:36.713
because he looks like
he's wearing a tuxedo,

14:36.715 --> 14:38.381
but I think you're right.

14:38.383 --> 14:41.418
Deep down he's a cheating,
flightless little bastard.

14:43.187 --> 14:45.889
Go on.

14:45.891 --> 14:48.324
If I were you, I'd go down to that zoo

14:48.326 --> 14:49.626
and see what he's up to.

14:49.628 --> 14:51.188
And if you have a
supportive girlfriend,

14:51.190 --> 14:52.430
maybe you could bring her, too.

14:52.454 --> 14:55.365
Charlotte from Manhattan,
that is a great idea.

14:55.367 --> 14:56.366
Thanks for calling.

14:56.368 --> 14:58.468
I'm gonna go get that penguin.

14:58.470 --> 15:00.570
Oscar? Oscar, you got...

15:00.572 --> 15:02.806
Oh, yeah, 40 minutes of show left.

15:14.761 --> 15:16.829
Do you really need sunglasses?

15:16.831 --> 15:18.965
I don't want The Ice
Man to recognize me.

15:20.334 --> 15:23.569
Ugh! Do penguins not have noses?

15:23.571 --> 15:26.138
OSCAR: Well,

15:26.140 --> 15:28.508
something definitely
smells fishy around here.

15:32.246 --> 15:33.579
I'm doing a Batman thing.

15:33.581 --> 15:36.682
Yeah, I got it. It's good.

15:38.485 --> 15:39.986
So...

15:39.988 --> 15:42.655
what's your theory on how
the penguins are cheating?

15:42.657 --> 15:44.524
Well, you see that bucket
of fish right there?

15:44.526 --> 15:46.325
Maybe somebody who knows
a lot about hockey

15:46.327 --> 15:48.895
is luring The Ice Man
through the right gate.

15:48.897 --> 15:49.862
But how do we bust them?

15:51.398 --> 15:53.165
Well, Batman would wait

15:53.167 --> 15:54.267
till the coast was clear,

15:54.269 --> 15:55.535
and then he'd scale this wall

15:55.537 --> 15:57.470
and catch the bad guys red-handed.

15:57.472 --> 16:00.606
Whoa. Maybe you're Batman.

16:00.608 --> 16:03.843
Uh, no, Oscar, that's your thing.

16:03.845 --> 16:05.678
No, I like it.

16:05.680 --> 16:08.514
I'm dating Batman.

16:08.516 --> 16:11.050
- Okay, come on.
- What?

16:11.052 --> 16:13.486
- Come on.
- In...

16:13.488 --> 16:17.223
It's a two-foot wall.
Scale it, scale it!

16:18.926 --> 16:23.729
Whoa. The smell is definitely
not getting better.

16:25.098 --> 16:26.978
MURPH: Hey, you guys set
up in your usual spots.

16:27.002 --> 16:27.900
- Murph's here!
- Hide!

16:27.902 --> 16:28.901
Hide, hide!

16:28.903 --> 16:31.203
Oh...

16:38.478 --> 16:40.479
Hey, Felix. Are you ready?

16:40.481 --> 16:42.715
I think so. Not totally sure.

16:42.717 --> 16:44.550
I've been thinking about it all day.

16:44.552 --> 16:46.632
I guess let's just proceed
and see what happens, hmm?

16:46.656 --> 16:48.455
(hesitantly): Okay.

16:49.356 --> 16:51.424
Well, um, just to make it

16:51.426 --> 16:53.492
a little more comfortable this time,

16:53.494 --> 16:55.027
do you mind if I put on some music?

16:55.029 --> 16:56.495
- Uh, okay, sure.
- Okay, great.

16:56.497 --> 16:57.630
- Of course.
- Ooh.

16:57.632 --> 16:59.632
Can I dim the lights a little?

17:00.901 --> 17:04.002
Ooh, maybe I'll pour some wine.

17:04.005 --> 17:05.137
It'll set the mood.

17:05.138 --> 17:07.607
Help us relax.

17:07.608 --> 17:09.141
(romantic music playing)

17:09.143 --> 17:12.578
Okay. (chuckles)

17:12.579 --> 17:14.646
Second time's a charm.

17:14.648 --> 17:16.648
Emily, I can't do this.

17:16.651 --> 17:18.317
No, you can relax.

17:18.319 --> 17:19.752
I saw you do it once.

17:22.356 --> 17:24.290
No, what I mean is...

17:24.291 --> 17:27.893
we can't get back together.

17:27.895 --> 17:29.729
W-Wait, what?

17:29.731 --> 17:31.849
I heard you say that you want me,

17:31.850 --> 17:33.531
and then you invented
a reason to come here

17:33.533 --> 17:34.766
for the second photo shoot,

17:34.768 --> 17:37.870
with the wine and the freaky sex music.

17:37.872 --> 17:38.871
Felix...

17:38.873 --> 17:41.574
(shushing)

17:43.010 --> 17:44.944
Don't embarrass yourself, kid.

17:44.946 --> 17:46.345
It's funny, a couple months ago

17:46.347 --> 17:48.347
this would have been exactly
what I was hoping for.

17:48.349 --> 17:50.229
But I know that since
our breakup, I have grown,

17:50.253 --> 17:52.218
and in my heart, I have moved on.

17:52.220 --> 17:54.687
And, yes, it was hard to get over.

17:54.689 --> 17:58.157
But I did it, and you can, too.

18:01.128 --> 18:02.695
Wow. (chuckles)

18:02.697 --> 18:07.066
You really put all that
together, didn't you?

18:08.402 --> 18:10.102
Uh, news flash,
when you want something,

18:10.104 --> 18:12.238
you are not a subtle woman.

18:12.240 --> 18:14.140
(laughs)

18:14.142 --> 18:16.942
You know what? You are right.

18:16.944 --> 18:18.310
Of course.

18:18.312 --> 18:21.047
- And I'm-I'm really glad that you
- Mm-hmm.

18:21.049 --> 18:24.750
Picked up on all my obvious clues,

18:24.752 --> 18:27.019
and didn't think this was all just some

18:27.021 --> 18:30.122
crazy ploy to get photos
for that Web site.

18:30.124 --> 18:33.192
As if.

18:33.194 --> 18:35.895
And since you kind of

18:35.897 --> 18:38.798
just broke up with me,

18:38.800 --> 18:41.434
now it's like we're even.

18:41.436 --> 18:44.303
I mean, now we can hang out as friends,

18:44.305 --> 18:46.172
and I don't have to feel bad

18:46.174 --> 18:48.407
about breaking up with you anymore.

18:48.409 --> 18:50.042
Yes. Emily,

18:50.044 --> 18:52.178
I'm setting you free.

18:52.180 --> 18:54.447
Oh...

18:54.449 --> 18:56.649
(chuckles)

18:56.651 --> 18:59.652
Well, I mean, since we're here,

18:59.654 --> 19:01.854
should we take some
pictures just for fun?

19:01.856 --> 19:04.690
Sure.

19:04.692 --> 19:06.792
Just as friends?

19:06.794 --> 19:09.428
Just as friends.

19:09.430 --> 19:12.765
Wait, don't move. You look perfect.

19:12.767 --> 19:14.467
(camera shutter clicks)

19:21.134 --> 19:23.366
- Are they still there?
- OSCAR: It may be a while.

19:23.367 --> 19:25.901
Murph's having trouble
pronouncing the word "Montreal""

19:27.404 --> 19:29.572
What's that?

19:29.574 --> 19:30.706
Um...

19:30.708 --> 19:33.042
Bat Juice.

19:33.044 --> 19:34.510
You okay?

19:34.512 --> 19:37.463
There's something I didn't tell you.

19:37.464 --> 19:39.764
Birds absolutely terrify me,

19:39.765 --> 19:42.332
with their pointy beaks
and their flesh-ripping talons.

19:42.334 --> 19:45.802
- I don't think...
- They used to be dinosaurs!

19:45.804 --> 19:47.905
Wow, you're really scared,

19:47.907 --> 19:50.807
and you still did this for me?

19:50.809 --> 19:53.176
Of course.

19:53.178 --> 19:54.378
I love you, Oscar.

19:54.380 --> 19:57.548
And I've got your back no matter what.

20:01.920 --> 20:03.887
(Oscar grunts)

20:03.889 --> 20:08.392
Pointy nails on my bone again.

20:08.394 --> 20:12.129
(whispering): Look behind you.

20:14.866 --> 20:17.868
So many birds.

20:17.870 --> 20:20.637
Okay, let's get you out of here.

20:20.639 --> 20:23.140
No, we can't go now.

20:23.142 --> 20:25.475
We still haven't figured out
how the penguins are cheating.

20:25.477 --> 20:26.957
And what if the camera crew sees you?

20:26.981 --> 20:28.579
Oh, I don't care about them anymore.

20:28.581 --> 20:30.681
All I care is that
Charlotte from Manhattan

20:30.683 --> 20:32.115
is on my side.

20:32.117 --> 20:34.818
Okay?

20:34.820 --> 20:36.119
Don't look directly at them.

20:39.791 --> 20:42.025
Oscar?

20:42.027 --> 20:43.293
Oh, guys,

20:43.295 --> 20:46.063
forget the "Mon-treel" segment,
shoot this.

20:47.165 --> 20:50.434
Oh, no, another one.

20:50.436 --> 20:51.902
(trills)

20:55.873 --> 20:57.941
Well, well, well...

20:57.943 --> 21:00.210
we finally meet face to face.

21:00.212 --> 21:02.713
You may think you're pretty cool,

21:02.715 --> 21:04.214
but you're just a penguin,

21:04.216 --> 21:05.949
and I'm Batman!

